verses.roman:
hena-kāle digvijayī tāhāṅi āilā
gaṅgāre vandana kari' prabhure mililā

synonyms: hena-kāle—at this time; dig-vijayī—Keśava Kāśmīrī; tāhāṅi—there; āilā—reached; gaṅgāre—to mother Ganges; vandana—prayers; kari'-offering; prabhure—the Lord; mililā—met.
translation: Coincidentally Keśava Kāśmīrī Paṇḍita also came there. While offering his prayers to mother Ganges, he met Caitanya Mahāprabhu.
